{{Infobox civilian attack | title = 2015 Fotokol attack | partof = Spillover of the [[Islamist insurgency in Nigeria]] | image = | caption = | location = Fotol Cameroon | target = | coordinates = | date = 4–5 February 2015 | time = | timezone = | type = Massacre, shooting, arson | fatalities = 91 / 100 | injuries = 500 | perps = [[Boko Haram]] | weapons = }} {{Campaignbox Nigerian Sharia conflict}}
The '''2015 Fotokol attack''' occurred on 4 and 5 February 2015 when [[Boko Haram]] militants reportedly killed at least 91 people by shooting and burning, and injured over 500 in [[Fotokol]], Cameroon. The militants also torched mosques and churches of the town.<ref>{{cite news|title=Boko Haram Shoot, Burn To Death Dozens Of Civilians In Cameroon|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/02/05/boko-haram-cameroon_n_6621180.html?ir=India|publisher=Huffington Post|accessdate=7 February 2015|date=5 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/04/us-nigeria-violence-chad-idUSKBN0L816820150204 |title=Boko Haram kill more than 100 in Cameroon: local leader |newspaper=Reuters |date=4 February 2015 |first=Madjiasra |last=Nako |first2=Matthew Mpoke |last2=Bigg |accessdate=12 October 2016}}</ref>
