{{Infobox company | name = Egyptian Natural Gas Holding Company (EGAS) | logo = | caption = | type = state-owned | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{start date and age|2001}} | founder = | defunct = | location_city = [[Nasr City]], [[Cairo]] | location_country = [[Egypt]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = [[Mohamed Ali al-Masry]] (Chairman)<ref>[https://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFKCN0X41IJ Egypt replaces heads of state oil and gas companies]</ref> | industry = [[oil and gas industry|Oil and gas]] | products = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = | assets = | equity = | owner = [[Ministry of Petroleum and Mineral Resources (Egypt)|Ministry of Petroleum]] | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{url|www.egas.com.eg}} | footnotes = | intl = }} The '''Egyptian Natural Gas Holding Company (EGAS)''' is an Egyptian state-owned holding company, which owns and manages state stakes in different gas project. The company was established in August 2001.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://egas.com.eg/Corporate_Overview/Introduction.aspx|title=EGAS|website=egas.com.eg|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref> EGAS is also responsible for issuing of natural gas exploration licenses in Egypt.<ref name=upstream160210>{{cite news|url=http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/article206577.ece|title=EGAS hands out exploration spoils|work=[[Upstream (newspaper)|Upstream Online]]|date=16 February 2010|accessdate=17 June 2010}}</ref>
==Operations== In 2014/2015, EGAS signed six agreements, of them three offshore areas in Mediterranean Sea and three onshore areas in Nile Delta. In February 2015, a bidding for twelve offshore blocks in Mediterranean Sea was announced.{{cn|date=May 2016}}
In 2014/2015, gas production reached about {{convert|1.65|e12cuft/a|abbr=off}} and total local consumption of natural gas reached {{convert|1.66|e12cuft/a|abbr=off}}. Gas import started in April 2015, supplying to the national gas grid after the regasification with quantity of {{convert|30|e9cuft|abbr=off}}.<ref>[http://egas.com.eg/docs/pdf/Egas_EN_2015_Final%20@3-9-2015.pdf EGAS Annual Report for FY 2014-2015]</ref> In 2012/2013, total net gas production in Egypt reached {{convert|2.26|e12cuft/a|abbr=off}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://egas.com.eg/Egyptian_Natural_Gas/Introduction.aspx|title=EGAS|website=egas.com.eg|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref><ref>[http://egas.com.eg/docs/pdf/Egas_EN_2015_Final%20@3-9-2015.pdf EGAS Annual Report for FY 2014-2015]</ref>
==Corporate affairs== In April 2016 Egyptian Oil Minister Tarek al-Molla replaced the Chairman of EGAS Khaled Abdel Badie by Mohamed Ali al-Masry who previously took place of the chairman of Egypt EPGC company.<ref>[https://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFKCN0X41IJ Egypt replaces heads of state oil and gas companies]</ref>
