'''Ishq FM''', branded as '''Ishq 104.8 FM''', (formerly '''Meow FM''' and '''OYE FM''') is a romantic music <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/kolkata-gets-its-first-romantic-radio-fm-station-116112201564_1.html|title=Kolkata gets its first romantic radio FM station|last=|first=|date=November 22, 2016|website=[[business-standard.com]]|publisher=[[Press Trust of India]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> [[FM broadcasting|FM]] Radio Channel in India that broadcasts in the major cities: [[Delhi]], [[Mumbai]], & [[Kolkata]]. It was initially launched as Meow FM, which was a talk-based channel and served [[Delhi]], [[Indore]], [[Mumbai]] and [[Kolkata]].<ref>[http://www.radioduniya.in/news/news-details.asp?News=Meow-FM-officially-launched-in-Kolkata&NewsID=11509&NewsCategeory=stations%20launched "Meow FM officially launched in Kolkata"], 8 October 2007.</ref> It is an [[India Today Group]] venture and its format was directed at a female audience. The channel got noticed for its catchy advertisement on BEST buses. It had also introduced ''"Meri Meow"'', a social network for its fans.<ref>[http://www.radioduniya.in/news/news-details.asp?News=Meow-launches-social-networking-platform&NewsID=14415&NewsCategeory=mobile/internet%20radio "Meow launches social networking platform"], 28 July 2008.</ref> In September 2010 the channel had changed its name to [[OYE-FM]] and programming to a [[Filmi]] format. In December 2016 it rechristened to the current avatar of ISHQ 104.8 FM.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/biz/radio/private-fm-stations/160908-oye-fm-turns-ishq-fm|title=Oye FM turns 'Ishq FM'|last=|first=|date=September 8, 2016|work=radioandmusic.com|access-date=2018-07-19|publisher=Indiantelevision Dot Com Pvt. Ltd.|language=en}}</ref>
==Channel Description== Ishq FM is India's first Romantic Radio Station airing over the FM frequency of 104.8 MHz. It airs era-agnostic Bollywood blockbusters from the romantic genre 24x7. The station’s catchy jingle "DO THE ISHQ, Baby” has been composed by Sachin-Jigar.
The brand will have a target audience of 25-34 year. ==See also== *[[FM broadcasting in India]] *[[List of FM radio stations in India]] *[[India Today Group]]
