{{dicdef}}A '''kavass''' or '''cavass''' is a [[Turkish language|Turkish]] name for an armed police-officer, also for a courier or guide such as it is usual to engage when travelling in [[Turkey]].<ref>{{EB1911 |wstitle=Kavass |volume=15 |page=701 |inline=1}}</ref>
The name is used, inter alia, for the guards that traditionally preserve public order at the important worship spots of the Holy Land (formerly under Ottoman Turkey jurisdiction), such as the [[Holy Sepulcher]] in Jerusalem and the [[Church of the Nativity|Nativity Church]] in Bethlehem.
