[[Image:Cambodia National road No.6.jpg|thumb|250px|National Highway 6]]
'''National Highway 6''' or National Road No.6 (10006) is one of the national [[highway]]s of [[Cambodia]]. It is {{convert|416|km|abbr=on}} long (including 6A), it connects the capital of [[Phnom Penh]] with [[Banteay Meanchey]] through [[Siem Reap]] on the north shore of the [[Tonlé Sap]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060825003757/http://www.cambodiaportal.com/index.php?mymenu=destinations&submenu=nationalroadnetwork&ext=Y&submenutitle=National%20Road%20Network Cambodian national road network]</ref> It terminates merging into the [[National Highway 5 (Cambodia)|National Highway 5]].

==National Highway 6A==
From Phnom Penh to the town of [[Skun]] ({{convert|73|km|abbr=on}}), where it connects with [[National Highway 7 (Cambodia)|National Highway 7]], the highway has been upgraded to [[dual carriageway]] and it bears the name of National Highway 6A.

