The '''New Democratic Front''' is a progressive [[political party]] in [[Botswana]] without parliamentary representation. Led by [[Dick Bayford]], it split away from the [[Botswana National Front]] in 2003. It won 0.78% of the popular votes at the last elections. After its poor performance in the 2004 general elections the party has since joined forces with Botswana's third largest party Botswana Congress party.

